175 static void MmwDemo_sensorStopEpilog(void)
176 {
177  Hwi_StackInfo stackInfo;
178  Task_Stat stat;
179  bool hwiStackOverflow;
180 
181  System_printf("Data Path Stopped (last frame processing done)\n");
182 
183  /* Print DSS task statistics */
184  System_printf("DSS Task Stack Usage (Note: Task Stack Usage) ==========\n");
185 
186  Task_stat(gMmwDssMCB.initTaskHandle, &stat);
187  System_printf("%20s %12d %12d %12d\n", "initTask",
188  stat.stackSize,
189  stat.used,
190  stat.stackSize - stat.used);
191 
192  Task_stat(gMmwDssMCB.objDetDpmTaskHandle, &stat);
193  System_printf("%20s %12s %12s %12s\n", "Task Name", "Size", "Used", "Free");

195  stat.stackSize,
196  stat.used,
197  stat.stackSize - stat.used);
198 
199  System_printf("HWI Stack (same as System Stack) Usage ============\n");

201  if (hwiStackOverflow == TRUE)

204  MmwDemo_debugAssert(0);
205  }
206  else
207  {
208  System_printf("%20s %12s %12s %12s\n", " ", "Size", "Used", "Free");

210  stackInfo.hwiStackSize,

236 static void MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_reportFxn
237 (
238  DPM_Report reportType,
239  uint32_t instanceId,
240  int32_t errCode,
241  uint32_t arg0,
242  uint32_t arg1
243 )
244 {
245 
246  /* Only errors are logged on the console: */
247  if (errCode != 0)
248  {
249  /* Error: Detected log on the console and die all errors are FATAL currently. */
250  System_printf ("Error: DPM Report %d received with error:%d arg0:0x%x arg1:0x%x\n",
251  reportType, errCode, arg0, arg1);
252  DebugP_assert (0);
253  }
254 
255  /* Processing further is based on the reports received: This is the control of the profile
256  * state machine: */
257  switch (reportType)
258  {
259  case DPM_Report_IOCTL:
260  {
261  /*****************************************************************
262  * DPC has been configured without an error:
263  * - This is an indication that the profile configuration commands
264  * went through without any issues.
265  *****************************************************************/
266  DebugP_log1("DSSApp: DPM Report IOCTL, command = %d\n", arg0);
267  break;
268  }
269  case DPM_Report_DPC_STARTED:
270  {
271  /*****************************************************************
272  * DPC has been started without an error:
273  * - notify sensor management task that DPC is started.
274  *****************************************************************/
275  DebugP_log0("DSSApp: DPM Report start\n");
276  break;
277  }
278  case DPM_Report_NOTIFY_DPC_RESULT:
279  {
280  /*****************************************************************
281  * DPC Results have been passed:
282  * - This implies that we have valid profile results which have
283  * been received from the profile.
284  *****************************************************************/
285 
286  break;
287  }
288  case DPM_Report_NOTIFY_DPC_RESULT_ACKED:
289  {
290  /*****************************************************************
291  * DPC Results have been acked:
292  * - This implies that MSS received the results.
293  *****************************************************************/
294 
295  break;
296  }
297  case DPM_Report_DPC_ASSERT:
298  {
299  DPM_DPCAssert* ptrAssert;
300 
301  /*****************************************************************
302  * DPC Fault has been detected:
303  * - This implies that the DPC has crashed.
304  * - The argument0 points to the DPC assertion information
305  *****************************************************************/
306  ptrAssert = (DPM_DPCAssert*)arg0;
307  System_printf ("DSS Exception: %s, line %d.\n", ptrAssert->fileName,
308  ptrAssert->lineNum);
309  break;
310  }
311  case DPM_Report_DPC_STOPPED:
312  {
313  /*****************************************************************
314  * DPC has been stopped without an error:
315  * - This implies that the DPC can either be reconfigured or
316  * restarted.
317  *****************************************************************/
318  DebugP_log0("DSSApp: DPM Report stop\n");
319 
320  MmwDemo_sensorStopEpilog();
321  break;
322  }
323  case DPM_Report_DPC_INFO:
324  {
325  /* Currently objDetHwa does not use this feature. */
326  break;
327  }
328  default:
329  {
330  DebugP_assert (0);
331  break;
332  }
333  }
334  return;
335 }

387  void MmwDemo_updateObjectDetStats
388 (
389  DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *currDpcStats,
390  MmwDemo_output_message_stats *outputMsgStats
391 )
392 {
393  static uint32_t prevInterFrameEndTimeStamp = 0U;
394 
395  /* Calculate interframe proc time */
396  outputMsgStats->interFrameProcessingTime =
397  (currDpcStats->interFrameEndTimeStamp - currDpcStats->interFrameStartTimeStamp)/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ; /* In micro seconds */
398 
399  outputMsgStats->interChirpProcessingMargin = currDpcStats->interChirpProcessingMargin/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ;
400 
401  /* Calculate interFrame processing Margin for previous frame, but saved to current frame */
402  outputMsgStats->interFrameProcessingMargin =
403  (currDpcStats->frameStartTimeStamp - prevInterFrameEndTimeStamp - currDpcStats->subFramePreparationCycles)/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ;
404 
405  prevInterFrameEndTimeStamp = currDpcStats->interFrameEndTimeStamp;
406 }

421 static int32_t MmwDemo_copyResultToHSRAM
422 (
423  MmwDemo_HSRAM *ptrHsramBuffer,
424  DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *result,
425  MmwDemo_output_message_stats *outStats
426 )
427 {
428  uint8_t *ptrCurrBuffer;
429  uint32_t totalHsramSize;
430  uint32_t itemPayloadLen;
431 
432  /* Save result in HSRAM */
433  if(ptrHsramBuffer == NULL)
434  {
435  return -1;
436  }
437 
438  /* Save result in HSRAM */
439  if(result != NULL)
440  {
441  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult);
442  memcpy((void *)&ptrHsramBuffer->result, (void *)result, itemPayloadLen);
443  }
444  else
445  {
446  return -1;
447  }
448 
449  /* Save output Stats in HSRAM */
450  if(outStats != NULL)
451  {
452  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
453  memcpy((void *)&ptrHsramBuffer->outStats, (void *)outStats, itemPayloadLen);
454  }
455 
456  /* Set payload pointer to HSM buffer */
457  ptrCurrBuffer = &ptrHsramBuffer->payload[0];
458  totalHsramSize = MMWDEMO_HSRAM_PAYLOAD_SIZE;
459 
460  /* Save ObjOut in HSRAM */
461  if(result->objOut != NULL)
462  {
463  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudCartesian) * result->numObjOut;
464  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
465  {
466  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->objOut, itemPayloadLen);
467 
468  ptrHsramBuffer->result.objOut = (DPIF_PointCloudCartesian *)ptrCurrBuffer;
469  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
470  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
471  }
472  else
473  {
474  return -1;
475  }
476  }
477 
478  /* Save ObjOutSideInfo in HSRAM */
479  if(result->objOutSideInfo != NULL)
480  {
481  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo) * result->numObjOut;
482  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
483  {
484  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->objOutSideInfo, itemPayloadLen);
485  ptrHsramBuffer->result.objOutSideInfo = (DPIF_PointCloudSideInfo *)ptrCurrBuffer;
486  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
487  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
488  }
489  else
490  {
491  return -1;
492  }
493  }
494 
495  /* Save DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats in HSRAM */
496  if(result->stats != NULL)
497  {
498  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats);
499  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
500  {
501  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->stats, itemPayloadLen);
502  ptrHsramBuffer->result.stats = (DPC_ObjectDetection_Stats *)ptrCurrBuffer;
503  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
504  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
505  }
506  else
507  {
508  return -1;
509  }
510  }
511 
512  /* Save compRxChanBiasMeasurement in HSRAM */
513  if(result->compRxChanBiasMeasurement != NULL)
514  {
515  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(DPU_AoAProc_compRxChannelBiasCfg);
516  if((totalHsramSize- itemPayloadLen) > 0)
517  {
518  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)result->compRxChanBiasMeasurement, itemPayloadLen);
519  ptrHsramBuffer->result.compRxChanBiasMeasurement = (DPU_AoAProc_compRxChannelBiasCfg *)ptrCurrBuffer;
520  ptrCurrBuffer+= itemPayloadLen;
521  totalHsramSize -=itemPayloadLen;
522  }
523  else
524  {
525  return -1;
526  }
527  }
528 
529  return totalHsramSize;
530 }

543 static void MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_dpmTask(UArg arg0, UArg arg1)
544 {
545  int32_t retVal;
546  DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *result;
547  volatile uint32_t startTime;
548 
549  while (1)
550  {
551  /* Execute the DPM module: */
552  retVal = DPM_execute (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle, &resultBuffer);
553  if (retVal < 0) {
554  System_printf ("Error: DPM execution failed [Error code %d]\n", retVal);
555  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
556  }
557  else
558  {
559  if ((resultBuffer.size[0] == sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult)))
560  {
561  result = (DPC_ObjectDetection_ExecuteResult *)resultBuffer.ptrBuffer[0];
562 
563  /* Get the time stamp before copy data to HSRAM */
564  startTime = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
565 
566  /* Update processing stats and added it to buffer 1*/
567  MmwDemo_updateObjectDetStats(result->stats,
568  &gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.subFrameStats[result->subFrameIdx]);
569 
570  /* Copy result data to HSRAM */
571  if ((retVal = MmwDemo_copyResultToHSRAM(&gHSRAM, result, &gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.subFrameStats[result->subFrameIdx])) >= 0)
572  {
573  /* Update interframe margin with HSRAM copy time */
574  gHSRAM.outStats.interFrameProcessingMargin -= ((Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - startTime)/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
575 
576  /* Update DPM buffer */
577  resultBuffer.ptrBuffer[0] = (uint8_t *)&gHSRAM.result;
578  resultBuffer.ptrBuffer[1] = (uint8_t *)&gHSRAM.outStats;
579  resultBuffer.size[1] = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
580 
581  /* YES: Results are available send them. */
582  retVal = DPM_sendResult (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle, true, &resultBuffer);
583  if (retVal < 0)
584  {
585  System_printf ("Error: Failed to send results [Error: %d] to remote\n", retVal);
586  }
587  }
588  else
589  {
590  System_printf ("Error: Failed to copy processing results to HSRAM, error=%d\n", retVal);
591  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
592  }
593  }
594  }
595  }
596 }

607 static void MmwDemo_dssInitTask(UArg arg0, UArg arg1)
608 {
609  int32_t errCode;
610  Task_Params taskParams;
611  DPM_InitCfg dpmInitCfg;
612  DPC_ObjectDetection_InitParams objDetInitParams;
613  uint32_t edmaCCIdx=0;
614 
615  /*****************************************************************************
616  * Driver Init:
617  *****************************************************************************/
618 
619  /* Initialize the Mailbox */
620  Mailbox_init(MAILBOX_TYPE_DSS);
621 
622  /*****************************************************************************
623  * Driver Open/Configuraiton:
624  *****************************************************************************/
625 
626  /* Initialize the Data Path: */
627  MmwDemo_dataPathInit(&gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj);
628  MmwDemo_dataPathOpen(&gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj);
629 
630  /*****************************************************************************
631  * Initialization of the DPM Module:
632  *****************************************************************************/
633  memset ((void *)&objDetInitParams, 0, sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_InitParams));
634 
635  /* Note this must be after MmwDemo_dataPathOpen() above which opens the hwa */
636  objDetInitParams.hwaHandle = gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.hwaHandle;
637  objDetInitParams.L3ramCfg.addr = (void *)&gMmwL3[0];
638  objDetInitParams.L3ramCfg.size = sizeof(gMmwL3);
639  objDetInitParams.CoreLocalRamCfg.addr = &gDPC_ObjDetL2Heap[0];
640  objDetInitParams.CoreLocalRamCfg.size = sizeof(gDPC_ObjDetL2Heap);
641  for (edmaCCIdx=0;edmaCCIdx<EDMA_NUM_CC;edmaCCIdx++)
642  {
643  objDetInitParams.edmaHandle[edmaCCIdx] = gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.edmaHandle[edmaCCIdx];
644  }
645 
646  /* DPC Call-back config */
647  objDetInitParams.processCallBackCfg.processFrameBeginCallBackFxn =
648  MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_processFrameBeginCallBackFxn;
649  objDetInitParams.processCallBackCfg.processInterFrameBeginCallBackFxn =
650  MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_processInterFrameBeginCallBackFxn;
651 
652  memset ((void *)&dpmInitCfg, 0, sizeof(DPM_InitCfg));
653 
654  /* Setup the configuration: */
655  dpmInitCfg.socHandle = gMmwDssMCB.socHandle;
656  dpmInitCfg.ptrProcChainCfg = &gDPC_ObjectDetectionCfg;
657  dpmInitCfg.instanceId = 0xFEEDFEED;
658  dpmInitCfg.domain = DPM_Domain_REMOTE;
659  dpmInitCfg.reportFxn = MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_reportFxn;
660  dpmInitCfg.arg = &objDetInitParams;
661  dpmInitCfg.argSize = sizeof(DPC_ObjectDetection_InitParams);
662 
663  /* Initialize the DPM Module: */
664  gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle = DPM_init (&dpmInitCfg, &errCode);
665  if (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle == NULL)
666  {
667  System_printf ("Error: Unable to initialize the DPM Module [Error: %d]\n", errCode);
668  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
669  return;
670  }
671 
672  /* Synchronization: This will synchronize the execution of the control module
673  * between the domains. This is a prerequiste and always needs to be invoked. */
674  while (1)
675  {
676  int32_t syncStatus;
677 
678  /* Get the synchronization status: */
679  syncStatus = DPM_synch (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj.objDetDpmHandle, &errCode);
680  if (syncStatus < 0)
681  {
682  /* Error: Unable to synchronize the framework */
683  System_printf ("Error: DPM Synchronization failed [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
684  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);
685  return;
686  }
687  if (syncStatus == 1)
688  {
689  /* Synchronization acheived: */
690  break;
691  }
692  /* Sleep and poll again: */
693  Task_sleep(1);
694  }
695  System_printf ("Debug: DPM Module Sync is done\n");
696 
697  /* Launch the DPM Task */
698  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);
699  taskParams.priority = MMWDEMO_DPC_OBJDET_DPM_TASK_PRIORITY;
700  taskParams.stackSize = 4*1024;
701  gMmwDssMCB.objDetDpmTaskHandle = Task_create(MmwDemo_DPC_ObjectDetection_dpmTask, &taskParams, NULL);
702 
703  return;
704 }

730 int main (void)

736

739

741  memset ((void *)&socCfg, 0, sizeof(SOC_Cfg));
742 
743  /* Populate the SOC configuration: */
744  socCfg.clockCfg = SOC_SysClock_BYPASS_INIT;
745 
746  /* Initialize the SOC Module: This is done as soon as the application is started
747  * to ensure that the MPU is correctly configured. */
748  socHandle = SOC_init (&socCfg, &errCode);
749  if (socHandle == NULL)

752  MmwDemo_debugAssert (0);

757

762 
763  /* Start BIOS */
